@startuml Seq08_ExpenseForecasting
!theme plain
participant User
participant "React Frontend" as Frontend
participant "Forecast API" as Backend
participant "Feature\nEngineering" as FeatureEng
participant "ML Model\n(Scikit-learn)" as MLModel
participant "MySQL DB" as DB

autonumber

Note over User,DB: **REQUEST FORECAST**

User -> Frontend: Navigate to Forecast
Frontend -> Frontend: Display forecast page
User -> Frontend: Select category: "Food"
User -> Frontend: Select forecast period: "3 months"
User -> Frontend: Click "Generate Forecast"

Frontend -> Backend: GET /forecast/predict?category_id=1&months=3

Backend -> DB: Fetch historical transactions
Backend -> DB: SELECT date, amount FROM transactions\nWHERE user_id AND category_id=1\nORDER BY date
DB --> Backend: [transaction_history]

Note over Backend: Historical data:
Note over Backend: Jan: 1850, Feb: 1920, Mar: 1780
Note over Backend: Apr: 1950, May: 2100

Backend --> Frontend: {status: "processing"}
Frontend -> Frontend: Show loading state

Note over User,DB: **FEATURE ENGINEERING**

Backend -> FeatureEng: engineer_features(transaction_history)

Note over FeatureEng: Feature Engineering:
FeatureEng -> FeatureEng: Extract temporal features
FeatureEng -> FeatureEng: - Month of year
FeatureEng -> FeatureEng: - Day of month
FeatureEng -> FeatureEng: - Seasonality indicators
FeatureEng -> FeatureEng: - Day of week pattern

FeatureEng -> FeatureEng: Calculate lag features
FeatureEng -> FeatureEng: - Last 1 month average
FeatureEng -> FeatureEng: - Last 3 month average
FeatureEng -> FeatureEng: - Last 6 month average
FeatureEng -> FeatureEng: - Trend direction

FeatureEng -> FeatureEng: Calculate rolling statistics
FeatureEng -> FeatureEng: - Rolling mean (30-day)
FeatureEng -> FeatureEng: - Rolling std dev
FeatureEng -> FeatureEng: - Momentum

FeatureEng -> FeatureEng: Handle seasonality
FeatureEng -> FeatureEng: - Detect seasonal patterns
FeatureEng -> FeatureEng: - Extract seasonal indices

Note over FeatureEng: Final Features Matrix:
Note over FeatureEng: X = [[month, lag_1m, lag_3m, rolling_mean, ...],
Note over FeatureEng:      [month, lag_1m, lag_3m, rolling_mean, ...],
Note over FeatureEng:      ...]
Note over FeatureEng: y = [1850, 1920, 1780, 1950, 2100]

FeatureEng --> Backend: {X: features_matrix, y: target_values}

Note over User,DB: **MODEL TRAINING**

Backend -> MLModel: train_forecast_model(X, y)

Note over MLModel: Model Options Available:
Note over MLModel: 1. Linear Regression (baseline)
Note over MLModel: 2. Random Forest (medium complexity)
Note over MLModel: 3. Gradient Boosting (advanced)

Note over MLModel: Using: Random Forest
MLModel -> MLModel: Split data: 80% train, 20% test
MLModel -> MLModel: Train on 80% historical data

Note over MLModel: Random Forest Steps:
MLModel -> MLModel: Build 100 decision trees
MLModel -> MLModel: Each tree on random feature subset
MLModel -> MLModel: Aggregate predictions

MLModel -> MLModel: Evaluate on test set
MLModel -> MLModel: Calculate metrics
Note over MLModel: - Mean Absolute Error: 85
Note over MLModel: - Root Mean Squared Error: 120
Note over MLModel: - R² Score: 0.87 (87% variance explained)

MLModel -> MLModel: Model trained and validated
MLModel --> Backend: {model: trained_model, metrics: {...}}

Note over User,DB: **GENERATE PREDICTIONS**

Backend -> MLModel: predict_future(model, periods=3)

Note over MLModel: Prediction Process:
MLModel -> MLModel: Generate future feature vectors

loop For Each Future Month (3 months)
    MLModel -> MLModel: Create features for future date
    MLModel -> MLModel: Use rolling statistics up to this point
    MLModel -> MLModel: Use estimated previous predictions
    
    MLModel -> MLModel: Pass through trained model
    MLModel -> MLModel: Get prediction
end

MLModel -> MLModel: June prediction: 2120 (±95 confidence interval)
MLModel -> MLModel: July prediction: 2180 (±110)
MLModel -> MLModel: August prediction: 2230 (±125)

Note over MLModel: Confidence intervals widening
Note over MLModel: as predictions go further in future

MLModel --> Backend: {predictions: [{month: "Jun", amount: 2120,\nci_lower: 2025, ci_upper: 2215},\n{month: "Jul", amount: 2180,\nci_lower: 2070, ci_upper: 2290}]}

Backend -> DB: INSERT INTO forecast_results\n(user_id, category_id, forecast_month,\npredicted_amount, confidence_lower,\nconfidence_upper, model_used, accuracy)
DB --> Backend: {forecast_ids}

Backend --> Frontend: {predictions: [...], accuracy: 0.87}

Note over User,DB: **DISPLAY FORECAST CHART**

Frontend -> Frontend: Prepare chart data

Note over Frontend: Chart combines:
Note over Frontend: - Historical data (line)
Note over Frontend: - Future predictions (dashed line)
Note over Frontend: - Confidence intervals (shaded area)

Frontend -> Frontend: Render forecast chart
Note over Frontend: X-axis: Months (Jan to Aug)
Note over Frontend: Y-axis: Spending Amount (₹)
Note over Frontend: Historical: Jan(1850)→May(2100)
Note over Frontend: Predicted: Jun(2120)→Aug(2230)
Note over Frontend: Shaded region: Confidence interval

Frontend --> User: Display forecast chart

Note over User,DB: **FORECAST INSIGHTS**

Backend -> Backend: Analyze forecast trends

Backend -> Backend: Trend analysis
Backend -> Backend: Growth rate: +1.6% per month
Backend -> Backend: Predicted avg (next 3 months): 2176
Backend -> Backend: vs. Last 3 months avg: 1920
Backend -> Backend: Increase: +256 (13.3%)

Backend -> Backend: Seasonal analysis
Backend -> Backend: June typically higher (pre-monsoon)
Backend -> Backend: August spike confirmed by pattern

Backend -> Backend: Generate insights

Backend --> Frontend: {forecast_insights:
Note over Backend: "1. Food spending trending upward (+1.6%/month)"
Note over Backend: "2. Expect ₹2,230 by August (13% increase)"
Note over Backend: "3. May need to increase Food budget to ₹2,250"
Note over Backend: "4. Monitor for seasonal spike in June"
}

Frontend -> Frontend: Display insights cards
Frontend --> User: Show forecast analysis

Note over User,DB: **EXPORT FORECAST**

User -> Frontend: Click "Export Forecast"
Frontend -> Frontend: Generate forecast report

Note over Frontend: Report includes:
Note over Frontend: - Chart visualization
Note over Frontend: - Numerical predictions
Note over Frontend: - Confidence intervals
Note over Frontend: - Insights and recommendations
Note over Frontend: - Model accuracy metrics

Frontend -> Frontend: Download as PDF/CSV
Frontend --> User: Forecast report downloaded

Note over User,DB: **RETRAINING & UPDATE**

Note over Backend: Monthly Retraining:
Note over Backend: - Every month, add new actual data
Note over Backend: - Remove oldest data (keep 12-24 months)
Note over Backend: - Retrain model with updated data
Note over Backend: - Evaluate accuracy improvement
Note over Backend: - Update predictions if accuracy improves

Backend -> Backend: Scheduled job every month
Backend -> MLModel: Retrain with latest data
Backend -> DB: Update forecast_results
Backend --> User: Notifications about updated forecasts

@enduml
